# Deploy to GitHub (aica)

Workflow follows the Git work cycle: work in your primary repository, then push to your public repository ([gitcore-tutorial](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcore-tutorial)).

## Repository

- **Remote**: `origin`
- **URL**: https://github.com/TaegyunKim-coder/aica.git
- **Default branch**: `main`

## Deploy as per Git (push to public repository)

1. **Prepare work repository** (one-time): already done via `git clone`; `origin` points to GitHub.
2. **Do your work** in this repo (e.g. Cursor-generated files under `aica`).
3. **Deploy = push to GitHub:**
   - Stage: `git add .` (or specific paths)
   - Commit: `git commit -m "Your message"`
   - Push: `git push origin main` (or `git push`)

## Before Pushing

- Run `git status` to see changes. Ensure only intended files are staged.
- If identity is needed: `git config user.name "TaegyunKim-coder"` and `git config user.email "TaegyunKim-coder@users.noreply.github.com"`

## When Asked to Deploy

- Run the deploy steps above in order.
- Use project root: `C:\Users\BioWiNS\aica` (or `aica` from workspace).
- Use PowerShell-compatible commands (e.g. `;` instead of `&&`).
